# Linux Ops Suite

> A personal Linux operations toolkit built from focused, single-purpose tools that work together through clean file-based contracts.

**This repository is the suite's contract & index headquarters — not a monorepo.** Each
tool lives in its own repo. Here you'll find the shared
[architecture](docs/ARCHITECTURE.md), the [integration map](docs/INTEGRATION_MAP.md),
the [contract rules](docs/CONTRACT_RULES.md), the [roadmap](docs/ROADMAP.md), the JSON
[`contracts/`](contracts/), and example [`examples/`](examples/).

---

## Tools

| Tool | Role | Status |
|---|---|---|
| [**Bulwark**](https://github.com/tom2025b/bulwark) | Read-only scanner and risk classifier — **source of truth for risk/inventory** | Active |
| [**ScriptVault**](https://github.com/tom2025b/scriptvault) | Fast fuzzy-search TUI script launcher with favorites and recents | Active |
| [**Bridge**](https://github.com/tom2025b/toolbox-bridge) | File-based connector that turns Bulwark risk data into ScriptVault sidecars | Active |
| [**ToolFoundry**](https://github.com/tom2025b/toolfoundry) | Lifecycle/ownership manager — **source of truth for lifecycle**; emits `rexops-feed` JSON | Active |
| [**Workstate**](https://github.com/tom2025b/workstate) | Read-only project/repository health dashboard | Architecture |
| [**RexOps**](https://github.com/tom2025b/rexops) | Operations cockpit — **the front door and only consumer** of all tool exports | In progress |

---

## How the Pieces Fit

Data flows one way: producers write files, **RexOps is the front door and final
consumer**. No tool imports another tool's code; no tool reads RexOps.

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph Producers
        B(Bulwark<br/>risk + inventory)
        T(ToolFoundry<br/>lifecycle)
        S(ScriptVault<br/>scripts)
        W(Workstate<br/>repo health)
    end
    B -->|risk| BR(Bridge)
    BR -->|sidecar YAML| S
    B -.->|scan JSON| R
    T ==>|rexops-feed JSON| R
    S -.->|export JSON| R
    W -.->|snapshot JSON| R
    R(["RexOps<br/>front door · consumer · launcher"])
```

Solid `==>` = a real, shipped contract today. Dotted `-.->` = planned (see the
[roadmap](docs/ROADMAP.md)). RexOps is the only consumer — it is where everything comes
together, and it never writes back into a tool.

---

## Design Principles

1. **One job per tool.** Each tool solves exactly one problem and stays inside that boundary.
2. **File-based contracts.** Tools communicate through JSON or YAML — never through shared code or direct calls.
3. **Read-only by default.** Tools that only need to observe never mutate.
4. **Offline and private.** No telemetry. No unnecessary network calls. XDG-compliant config.
5. **Low-resource.** Built to run well on a modest Linux machine without competing for headroom.
6. **Rust-first.** Chosen for performance, safety, and long-term reliability.

